page.content:
DELAMERE/EDDISBURY
GENERAL REVIEW THE TWELVE KILOMETRE SQUARE AREA DESCRIBED SUSEQUENTLY IS COVERED BY A FOREST WHICH OCCUPIES APPROXIMATELY FOUR & A HALF KILOMETRES. THE REMAINING LAND COVER IS AGRICULTURAL,MAINLY DAIRY FARMS,BUT WITH A FRUIT FARM ALSO. THERE IS A RAILWAY STATION,AN OUTDOOR EDUCATION CENTRE,A PLANT NURSERY & A BUSY CAFE AS WELL.OUR AREA IS BETWEEN THE SETTLEMENTS OF KELSALL,CUDDINGTON,KINGSLEY & MOULDSWORTH.THERE ARE NO LARGE AREAS OF DWELLINGS BUT THERE ARE SCATTERED GROUPS OF HOUSES LOCATED MAINLY ALONG THE TWO ROADS BISECTING THE AREA.
